obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (30159)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908&sectionId=30159&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Special Marriage`
  line `Act, 1954.`
  line
  line `((2) It extends to the whole of India ^1***, and applies also to citizens of India domiciled in the`
  line `territories to which this Act extends who are ^2[in the State of Jammu and Kashmir].`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^3 as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words except the State of Jammu and Kashmir omitted by Act 34 of 2019, s. 95 and the Fifth Schedule`
  line `(w.e.f. 31-10-2019).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 33 of 1969, s. 29, for outside the said territories (w.e.f. 31-8-1969).`
  line
  line `3. 1st January, 1955, vide notification No. S.R.O. 3606, dated 17th December, 1954, published in the Gazette of India,`
  line `Extraordinary, Part II, Section 3.`
  line
  line `The Act has been extended to State of Sikkim vide notification No. S.O. 1629(E), dated 15th April 2021, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II, sec. 3 (ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (30160)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908&sectionId=30160&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `^1* * * * *`
  line
  line `(b) "degrees of prohibited relationship"-a man and any of the persons mentioned in Part I of the`
  line `First Schedule and a woman and any of the persons mentioned in Part II of the said Schedule are`
  line `within the degrees of prohibited relationship.`
  line
  line `Explanation I.-- Relationship includes,--`
  line
  line `(a) relationship by half or uterine blood as well as by full blood;`
  line
  line `(b) illegitimate blood relationship as well as legitimate;`
  line
  line `(c) relationship by adoption as well as by blood;`
  line
  line `and all terms of relationship in this Act shall be construed accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation II.-- "Full blood" and "half blood" "two persons are said to be related to each other by`
  line `full blood when they are descended from a common ancestor by the same wife and by half blood when`
  line `they are descended from a common ancestor but by different wives.`
  line
  line `Explanation III.-- "Uterine blood" "two persons are said to be related to each other by uterine blood`
  line `when they are descended from a common ancestress but by different husbands.`
  line
  line `Explanation IV.-- In Explanations II and III, ancestor includes the father and "ancestress" the`
  line mother;
  line
  line `^2* * * * *`
  line
  line `(d) "district" in relation to a Marriage Officer, means the area for which he is appointed as such`
  line `under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) of section 3;`
  line
  line `^3[(e) "district court" means, in any area for which there is a city civil court, that court, and in any`
  line `other area, the principal civil court of original jurisdiction, and includes any other civil court which may be specified by the State Government by notification in the Official Gazette as having`
  line `jurisdiction in respect of the matters dealt with in this Act;]`
  line
  line `(f) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `^4[(g) "State Government", in relation to a Union territory, means the administrator thereof.]`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Omitted by Act 33 of 1969, s. 29.`
  line
  line `2. Omitted by s. 29, ibid.`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 68 of 1976, s. 20, for clause (e) (w.e.f. 27-5-1976).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by the A.O. (No. 3) Order, 1956 for clause (g).`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (30161)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Marriage Officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 33 of 1969, s. 29, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 31-8-1969).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908&sectionId=30161&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purposes of this Act, the State Government may, by, notification`
  line `in the Official Gazette, appoint one or more Marriage Officers for the whole or any part of the State.`
  line
  line `^1[(2) For the purposes of this Act, in its application to citizens of India domiciled in the territories to`
  line `which this Act extends who are in the State of Jammu and Kashmir, the Central Government may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, specify such officers of the Central Government as it may think fit to`
  line `be the Marriage Officers for the State or any part thereof.]`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (30162)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Conditions relating to solemnization of special marriages.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908&sectionId=30162&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in any other law for the time being in force relating to the solemnization of marriages, a`
  line `marriage between any two persons may be solemnized under this Act, if at the time of the marriage the`
  line `following conditions are fulfilled, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) neither party has a spouse living;`
  line
  line `^1[(b) neither party--`
  line
  line `(i) is incapable of giving a valid consent to it in consequence of unsoundness of mind; or`
  line
  line `(ii) though capable of giving a valid consent, has been suffering from mental disorder of such`
  line `a kind or to such an extent as to be unfit for marriage and the procreation of children; or`
  line
  line `(iii) has been subject to recurrent attacks of insanity ^2* * *;]`
  line
  line `(c) the male has completed the age of twenty-one years and the female the age of eighteen years;`
  line
  line `^3[(d) the parties are not within the degrees of prohibited relationship:`
  line
  line `Provided that where a custom governing at least one of the parties permits of a marriage between`
  line `them, such marriage may be solemnized, notwithstanding that they are within the degrees of`
  line `prohibited relationship; and`
  line
  line `^4[(e) where the marriage is solemnized in the State of Jammu and Kashmir, both parties are`
  line `citizens of India domiciled in the territories to which this Act extends.]`
  line
  line `^5[Explanation.-- In this section, "custom", in relation to a person belonging to any tribe, community,`
  line `group or family, means any rule which the State Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `specify in this behalf as applicable to members of that tribe, community, group or family:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such notification shall be issued in relation to the members of any tribe, community,`
  line `group or family, unless the State Government is satisfied--`
  line
  line `(i) that such rule has been continuously and uniformly observed for a long time among those`
  line members;
  line
  line `(ii) that such rule is certain and not unreasonable or opposed to public policy; and`
  line
  line `(iii) that such rule, if applicable only to a family, has not been discontinued by the family.]`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 68 of 1976, s. 21, for clause (b) (w.e.f. 27-5-1976).`
  line
  line `2. The words "or epilepsy" omitted by Act 39 of 1999, s. 4 (w.e.f. 29-12-1999).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 32 of 1963, s. 2, for clause (d) (w.e.f. 22-9-1963).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 33 of 1969, s. 29, for clause (e) (w.e.f. 31-8-1969).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Act 32 of 1963, s. 2 (w.e.f. 22-9-1963).`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (30163)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Notice of intended marriage.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908&sectionId=30163&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `When a marriage is intended to be solemnized under this Act, the`
  line `parties to the marriage shall give notice thereof in writing in the form specified in the Second Schedule to`
  line `the Marriage Officer of the district in which at least one of the parties to the marriage has resided for a`
  line `period of not less than thirty days immediately preceding the date on which such notice is given.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (30164)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Marriage Notice Book and publication.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908&sectionId=30164&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Marriage Officer shall keep all notices given`
  line `under section 5 with the records of his office and shall also forthwith enter a true copy of every such`
  line `notice in a book prescribed for that purpose, to be called the Marriage Notice Book, and such book shall`
  line `be open for inspection at all reasonable times, without fee, by any person desirous of inspecting the same.`
  line
  line `(2) The Marriage Officer shall cause every such notice to be published by affixing a copy thereof to`
  line `some conspicuous place in his office.`
  line
  line `(3) Where either of the parties to an intended marriage is not permanently residing within the local`
  line `limits of the district of the Marriage Officer to whom the notice has been given under section 5, the`
  line `Marriage Officer shall also cause a copy of such notice to be transmitted to the Marriage Officer of the`
  line `district within whose limits such party is permanently residing, and that Marriage Officer shall thereupon`
  line `cause a copy thereof to be affixed to some conspicuous place in his office.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (30165)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Objection to marriage.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908&sectionId=30165&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person may, before the expiration of thirty days from the date`
  line `on which any such notice has been published under sub-section (2) of section 6, object to the marriage on`
  line `the ground that it would contravene one or more of the conditions specified in section 4.`
  line
  line `(2) After the expiration of thirty days from the date on which notice of an intended marriage has been`
  line `published under sub-section (2) of section 6, the marriage may be solemnized, unless it has been`
  line `previously objected to under sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(3) The nature of the objection shall be recorded in writing by the Marriage Officer in the Marriage`
  line `Notice Book, be read over and explained if necessary, to the person making the objection and shall be`
  line `signed by him or on his behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (30166)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Procedure on receipt of objection.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908&sectionId=30166&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) If an objection is made under section 7 to an intended`
  line `marriage, the Marriage Officer shall not solemnize the marriage until he has inquired into the matter of`
  line `the objection and is satisfied that it ought not to prevent the solemnization of the marriage or the objection`
  line `is withdrawn by the person making it; but the Marriage Officer shall not take more than thirty days from`
  line `the date of the objection for the purpose of inquiring into the matter of the objection and arriving at a`
  line decision.
  line
  line `(2) If the Marriage Officer upholds the objection and refuses to solemnize the marriage, either party`
  line `to the intended marriage may, within a period of thirty days from the date of such refusal, prefer an appeal`
  line `to the district court within the local limits of whose jurisdiction the Marriage Officer has his office, and`
  line `the decision of the district court on such appeal shall be final, and the Marriage Officer shall act in`
  line `conformity with the decision of the court.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (30167)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Powers of Marriage Officers in respect of inquiries.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908&sectionId=30167&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purpose of any inquiry under`
  line `section 8, the Marriage Officer shall have all the powers vested in a civil court under the Code of Civil`
  line `Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), when trying a suit in respect of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) summoning and enforcing the attendance of witnesses and examining them on oath;`
  line
  line `(b) discovery and inspection;`
  line
  line `(c) compelling the production of documents;`
  line
  line `(d) reception of evidence of affidavits; and`
  line
  line `(e) issuing commissions for the examination of witnesses;`
  line
  line `and any proceeding before the Marriage Officer shall be deemed to be a judicial proceeding within the`
  line `meaning of section 193 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purpose of enforcing the attendance of any person to give evidence, the local`
  line `limits of the jurisdiction of the Marriage Officer shall be the local limits of his district.`
  line
  line `(2) If it appears to the Marriage Officer that the objection made to an intended marriage is not`
  line `reasonable and has not been made in good faith he may impose on the person objecting costs by way of`
  line `compensation not exceeding one thousand rupees and award the whole or any part thereof, to the parties`
  line `to the intended marriage, and any order for costs so made may be executed in the same manner as a`
  line `decree passed by the district court within the local limits of whose jurisdiction the Marriage Officer has`
  line `his office.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (30168)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Procedure on receipt of objection by Marriage Officer abroad.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908&sectionId=30168&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `Where an objection is made`
  line `under section 7 to a Marriage Officer ^1 [n the State of Jammu and Kashmir in respect of an intended`
  line `marriage in the State], and the Marriage Officer, after making such inquiry into the matter as he thinks fit,`
  line `entertains a doubt in respect thereof, he shall not solemnize the marriage but shall transmit the record with`
  line `such statement respecting the matter as he thinks fit to the Central Government, and the Central`
  line `Government, after making such inquiry into the matter and after obtaining such advice as it thinks fit,`
  line `shall give its decision thereon in writing to the Marriage Officer who shall act in conformity with the`
  line `decision of the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 33 of 1969, s. 29, for "outside the territories to which this Act extends in respect of an intended marriage outside`
  line `the said territories" (w.e.f. 31-8-1969).`
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (30169)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Declaration by parties and witnesses.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908&sectionId=30169&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `Before the marriage is solemnized the parties and three`
  line `witnesses shall, in the presence of the Marriage Officer, sign a declaration in the form specified in the`
  line `Third Schedule to this Act, and the declaration shall be countersigned by the Marriage Officer.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (30170)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Place and form of solemnization.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908&sectionId=30170&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) The marriage may be solemnized at the office of the`
  line `Marriage Officer, or at such other place within a reasonable distance therefrom as the parties may desire,`
  line `and upon such conditions and the payment of such additional fees as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The marriage may be solemnized in any form which the parties may choose to adopt:`
  line
  line `Provided that it shall not be complete and binding on the parties unless each party says to the other in`
  line `the presence of the Marriage Officer and the three witnesses and in any language understood by the`
  line `parties,-- "I, (A), take the (B), to be my lawful wife (or husband)".`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (30171)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Certificate of marriage.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908&sectionId=30171&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) When the marriage has been solemnized, the Marriage Officer`
  line `shall enter a certificate thereof in the form specified in the Fourth Schedule in a book to be kept by him`
  line `for that purpose and to be called the Marriage Certificate Book and such certificate shall be signed by the`
  line `parties to the marriage and the three witnesses.`
  line
  line `(2) On a certificate being entered in the Marriage Certificate Book by the Marriage Officer, the`
  line `Certificate shall be deemed to be conclusive evidence of the fact that a marriage under this Act has been`
  line `solemnized and that all formalities respecting the signatures of witnesses have been complied with.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (30172)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `New notice when marriage not solemnized within three months.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908&sectionId=30172&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `Whenever a marriage is not`
  line `solemnized within three calendar months from the date on which notice thereof has been given to the`
  line `Marriage Officer as required by section 5, or where an appeal has been filed under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 8, within three months from the date of the decision of the district court on such appeal or, where`
  line `the record of a case has been transmitted to the Central Government under section 10, within three months`
  line `from the date of decision of the Central Government, the notice and all other proceedings arising`
  line `therefrom shall be deemed to have lapsed, and no Marriage Officer shall solemnize the marriage until a`
  line `new notice has been given in the manner laid down in this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (30173)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Registration of marriages celebrated in other forms.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908&sectionId=30173&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `Any marriage celebrated, whether`
  line `before or after the commencement of this Act, other than a marriage solemnized under the Special Marriage Act, 1872 (3 of 1872), or under this Act, may be registered under this Chapter by a Marriage`
  line `Officer in the territories to which this Act extends if the following conditions are fulfilled, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) a ceremony of marriage has been performed between the parties and they have .been living`
  line `together as husband and wife ever since;`
  line
  line `(b) neither party has at the time of registration more than one spouse living;`
  line
  line `(c) neither party is an idiot or a lunatic at the time of registration;`
  line
  line `(d) the parties have completed the age of twenty-one years at the time of registration;`
  line
  line `(e) the parties are not within the degrees of prohibited relationship:`
  line
  line `Provided that in the case of a marriage celebrated before the commencement of this Act, this`
  line `condition shall be subject to any law, custom or usage having the force of law governing each of them`
  line `which permits of a marriage between the two; and`
  line
  line `(f) the parties have been residing within the district of the Marriage Officer for a period of not less`
  line `than thirty days immediately preceding the date on which the application is made to him for`
  line `registration of the marriage.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (30174)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Procedure for registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908&sectionId=30174&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `Upon receipt of an application signed by both the parties to the`
  line `marriage for the registration of their marriage under this Chapter the Marriage Officer shall give public`
  line `notice thereof in such manner as may be prescribed and after allowing a period of thirty days for`
  line `objections and after hearing any objection received within that period, shall, if satisfied that all the`
  line `conditions mentioned in section 15 are fulfilled, enter a certificate of the marriage in the Marriage`
  line `Certificate Book in the form specified in the Fifth Schedule, and such certificate shall be signed by the`
  line `parties to the marriage and by three witnesses.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (30175)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Appeals from orders under section 16.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908&sectionId=30175&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `Any person aggrieved by any order of a Marriage`
  line `Officer refusing to register a marriage under this Chapter may, within thirty days from the date of the`
  line `order, appeal against that order to the district court within the local limits of whose jurisdiction the`
  line `Marriage Officer has his office, and the decision of the district court on such appeal shall be final, and the`
  line `Marriage Officer to whom the application was made shall act in conformity with such decision.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (30176)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Effect of registration of marriage under this Chapter.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908&sectionId=30176&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions contained in`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 24, where a certificate of marriage has been finally entered in the Marriage`
  line `Certificate Book under this Chapter, the marriage shall, as from the date of such entry, be deemed to be a`
  line `marriage solemnized under this Act, and all children born after the date of the ceremony of marriage`
  line `(whose names shall also be entered in the Marriage Certificate Book) shall in all respects be deemed to be`
  line `and always to have been the legitimate children of their parents:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this section shall be construed as conferring upon any such`
  line `children any rights in or to the property of any person other than their parents in any case where, but for`
  line `the passing of this Act, such children would have been incapable of possessing or acquiring any such`
  line `rights by reason of their not being the legitimate children of their parents.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (30177)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Effect of marriage on member of undivided family.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908&sectionId=30177&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `The marriage solemnized under this Act`
  line `of any member of an undivided family who professes the Hindu, Buddhist, Sikh or Jaina religions shall be`
  line `deemed to effect his severance from such family.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (30178)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Rights and disabilities not affected by Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908&sectionId=30178&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of section 19, any person`
  line `whose marriage is solemnized under this Act shall have the same rights and shall be subject to the same`
  line `disabilities in regard to the right of succession to any property as a person to whom the Caste Disabilities`
  line `Removal Act, 1850 (21 of 1850), applies.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (30179)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Succession to property of parties married under Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908&sectionId=30179&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding any restrictions`
  line `contained in the Indian Succession Act, 1925 (39 of 1925), with respect to its application to members of certain communities, succession to the property or any person whose marriage is solemnized under this`
  line `Act and to the property of the issue of such marriage shall be regulated by the provisions of the said Act`
  line `and for the purposes of this Act shall have effect as if Chapter III of Part V (Special Rules for Parsi`
  line `Intestates) had been omitted therefrom.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21_a:
  sectionId (30180)
  sectionNo 21A
  orderNo 22
  title `Special provision in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 68 of 1976, s. 22 (w.e.f. 27-5-1976).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908&sectionId=30180&sectionno=21A&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908
obj_root_law_sections_21_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[21A. Special provision in certain cases.-- Where the marriage is solemnized under this Act of any`
  line `person who professes the Hindu, Buddhist, Sikh or Jaina religion with a person who professes the Hindu,`
  line `Buddhist, Sikh or Jaina religion, section 19 and section 21 shall not apply and so much of section 20 as`
  line `creates a disability shall also not apply.]`
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (30181)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 23
  title `Restitution of conjugal rights.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes `1. Added by s. 23, ibid.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908&sectionId=30181&sectionno=22&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `When either the husband or the wife has, without reasonable`
  line `excuse, withdrawn from the society of the other, the aggrieved party may apply by petition to the district`
  line `court for restitution of conjugal rights, and the court, on being satisfied of the truth of the statements made`
  line `in such petition, and that there is no legal ground why the application should not be granted, may decree`
  line `restitution of conjugal rights accordingly.`
  line
  line `^1[Explanation.-- Where a question arises whether there has been reasonable excuse for withdrawal`
  line `from the society, the burden of providing reasonable excuse shall be on the person who has withdrawn`
  line `from the society.]`
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (30182)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 24
  title `Judicial separation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908&sectionId=30182&sectionno=23&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) A petition for judicial separation may be presented to the district court`
  line `either by the husband or the wife,--`
  line
  line `(a) on any of the grounds specified ^1[in sub-section (1) ^2[and sub-section (1A)] of section 27] on`
  line `which a petition for divorce might have been presented; or`
  line
  line `(b) on the ground of failure to comply with a decree for restitution of conjugal rights;`
  line
  line `and the court, on being satisfied of the truth of the statements made in such petition, and that there is no`
  line `legal ground why the application should not be granted, may decree judicial separation accordingly.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the court grants a decree for judicial separation, it shall be no longer obligatory for the`
  line `petitioner to cohabit with the respondent, but the court may, on the application by petition of either party`
  line `and on being satisfied of the truth of the statements made in such petition, rescind the decree if it`
  line `considers it just and reasonable to do so.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 29 of 1970, s. 2, for certain words (w.e.f. 12-8-1970).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 68 of 1976, s. 24 (w.e.f. 27-5-1976).`
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (30183)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 25
  title `Void marriages.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 25, ibid., for "and may be so declared" (w.e.f. 27-5-1976).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908&sectionId=30183&sectionno=24&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any marriage solemnized under this Act shall be null and void ^1[and may,`
  line `on a petition presented by either party thereto against the other party, be so declared] by a decree of`
  line `nullity if--`
  line
  line `(i) any of the conditions specified in clauses (a), (b), (c) and (d) of section 4 has not been`
  line `fulfilled; or`
  line
  line `(ii) the respondent was impotent at the time of the marriage and at the time of the institution of`
  line `the suit.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing contained in this section shall apply to any marriage deemed to be solemnized under this`
  line `Act within the meaning of section 18, but the registration of any such marriage under Chapter III may be`
  line `declared to be of no effect if the registration was in contravention of any of the conditions specified in`
  line `clauses (a) to (e) of section 15:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such declaration shall be made in any case where an appeal has been preferred under`
  line `section 17 and the decision of the district court has become final.`
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (30184)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 26
  title `Voidable marriages.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908&sectionId=30184&sectionno=25&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `Any marriage solemnized under this Act shall be voidable and may be`
  line `annulled by a decree of nullity if,--`
  line
  line `(i) the marriage has not been consummated owing to the wilful refusal of the respondent to`
  line `consummate the marriage; or`
  line
  line `(ii) the respondent was at the time of the marriage pregnant by some person other than the`
  line `petitioner; or`
  line
  line `(iii) the consent of either party to the marriage was obtained by coercion or fraud, as defined in`
  line `the Indian Contract Act, 1872 (9 of 1872):`
  line
  line `Provided that, in the case specified in clause (ii), the court shall not grant a decree unless it is`
  line satisfied,--
  line
  line `(a) that the petitioner was at the time of the marriage ignorant of the facts alleged;`
  line
  line `(b) that proceedings were instituted within a year from the date of the marriage; and`
  line
  line `(c) that marital intercourse with the consent of the petitioner has not taken place since the`
  line `discovery by the petitioner of the existence of the grounds for a decree:`
  line
  line `Provided further that in the case specified in clause (iii), the court shall not grant a decree if,--`
  line
  line `(a) proceedings have not been instituted within one year after the coercion had ceased or, as the`
  line `case may be, the fraud had been discovered; or`
  line
  line `(b) the petitioner has with his or her free consent lived with the other party to the marriage as`
  line `husband and wife after the coercion had ceased or, as the case may be, the fraud had been discovered.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (30185)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 27
  title `Legitimacy of children of void and voidable marriages.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 68 of 1976, s. 26, for section 26 (w.e.f. 27-5-1976).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908&sectionId=30185&sectionno=26&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `^1[26. Legitimacy of children of void and voidable marriages.-- (1) Notwithstanding that a marriage`
  line `is null and void under section 24, any child of such marriage who would have been legitimate if the`
  line `marriage had been valid, shall be legitimate, whether such child is born before or after the commencement`
  line `of the Marriage Laws (Amendment) Act, 1976 (68 of 1976), and whether or not a decree of nullity is`
  line `granted in respect of that marriage under this Act and whether or not the marriage is held to be void`
  line `otherwise than on a petition under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a decree of nullity is granted in respect of a voidable marriage under section 25, any child`
  line `begotten or conceived before the decree is made, who would have been the legitimate child of the parties`
  line `to the marriage if at the date of the decree it has been dissolved instead of being annulled, shall be deemed`
  line `to be their legitimate child notwithstanding the decree of nullity.`
  line
  line `(3) Nothing contained in sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) shall be construed as conferring upon any`
  line `child of a marriage which is null and void or which is annulled by a decree of nullity under section 25,`
  line `any rights in or to the property of any person, other than the parents, in any case where, but for the`
  line `passing of this Act, such child would have been incapable of possessing or acquiring any such rights by`
  line `reason of not his being the legitimate child of his parents.]`
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (30186)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 28
  title Divorce.
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908&sectionId=30186&sectionno=27&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1)] Subject to the provisions of this Act and to the rules made thereunder, a petition`
  line `for divorce may be presented to the district court either by the husband or the wife on the ground that the`
  line respondent--
  line
  line `^2[(a) has, after the solemnization of the marriage, had voluntary sexual intercourse with any`
  line `person other than his or her spouse; or`
  line
  line `(b) has deserted the petitioner for a continuous period of not less than two years immediately`
  line `preceding the presentation of the petition; or]`
  line
  line `(c) is undergoing a sentence of imprisonment for seven years or more for an offence as defined in`
  line `the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860);`
  line
  line `^3* * * * *`
  line
  line `(d) has since the solemnization of the marriage treated the petitioner with cruelty; or`
  line
  line `^4[(e) has been incurably of unsound mind, or has been suffering continuously or intermittently`
  line `from mental disorder of such a kind and to such an extent that the petitioner cannot reasonably be`
  line `expected to live with the respondent.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- In this clause,--`
  line
  line `(a) the expression "mental disorder" means mental illness, arrested or incomplete`
  line `development of mind, psychopathic disorder or any other disorder or disability of mind and`
  line `includes schizophrenia;`
  line
  line `(b) the expression "psychopathic disorder" means a persistent disorder or disability of mind`
  line `(whether or not including sub-normality of intelligence) which results in abnormally aggressive`
  line `or seriously irresponsible conduct on the part of the respondent, and whether or not it requires or`
  line `is susceptible to medical treatment; or`
  line
  line `(f) has been suffering from venereal disease in a communicable form; or]`
  line
  line `^5* * * * *`
  line
  line `(h) has not been heard of as being alive for a period of seven years or more by those persons who`
  line `would naturally have heard of the respondent if the respondent had been alive; ^6* * *`
  line
  line `^7[Explanation.-- In this sub-section, the expression desertion means desertion of the petitioner by`
  line `the other party to the marriage without reasonable cause and without the consent or against the wish of`
  line `such party, and includes the wilful neglect of the petitioner by the other party to the marriage, and its`
  line `grammatical variations and cognate expressions shall be construed accordingly;`
  line
  line `^8* * * * *`
  line
  line `^9* * * * *`
  line
  line `^10[(1A) A wife may also present a petition for divorce to the district court on the ground,--`
  line
  line `(i) that her husband has, since the solemnization of the marriage, been guilty of rape, sodomy or`
  line bestiality;
  line
  line `(ii) that in a suit under section 18 of the Hindu Adoptions and Maintenance Act, 1956 (78 of`
  line `1956), or in a proceeding under section 125 of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974) (or`
  line `under the corresponding section 488 of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1898) (5 of 1898), a decree`
  line `or order, as the case may be, has been passed against the husband awarding maintenance to the wife`
  line `notwithstanding that she was living apart and that since the passing of such decree or order,`
  line `cohabitation between the parties has not been resumed for one year or upwards.`
  line
  line `^11[(2) Subject to the provisions of this Act and to the rules made thereunder, either party to a marriage,`
  line `whether solemnized before or after the commencement of the Special Marriage (Amendment) Act, 1970`
  line `(29 of 1970), may present a petition for divorce to the district court on the ground--`
  line
  line `(i) that there has been no resumption of cohabitation as between the parties to the marriage for a`
  line `period of one year or upwards after the passing of a decree for judicial separation in a proceeding to`
  line `which they were parties; or`
  line
  line `(ii) that there has been no restitution of conjugal rights as between the parties to the marriage for a`
  line `period of one year or upwards after the passing of a decree for restitution of conjugal rights in a`
  line `proceeding to which they were parties.]`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Section 27 renumbered as sub-section (1) thereof by Act 29 of 1970, s. 3 (w.e.f. 12-8-1970).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 68 of 1976, s. 27, for clauses (a) and (b).`
  line
  line `3. The Proviso omitted by Act 68 of 1976, s. 27 (w.e.f. 27-5-1976).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 27, ibid., for clauses (e) and (f) (w.e.f. 27-5-1976).`
  line
  line `5. Clause (g) omitted by Act 6 of 2019, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-3-2019).`
  line
  line `6. The word or omitted by Act 29 of 1970, s. 3 (w.e.f. 12-8-1970).`
  line
  line `7. Ins. by Act 68 of 1976, s. 27 (w.e.f. 27-5-1976).`
  line
  line `8. The words and by the wife on the ground that her husband has, since the solemnization of the marriage, been guilty of rape,`
  line `sodomy or bestiality omitted by s. 27, ibid. (w.e.f. 27-5-1976).`
  line
  line `9. Omitted by Act 29 of 1970), s. 3 (w.e.f. 12-8-1970).`
  line
  line `10. Ins. by Act 68 of 1976, s. 27 (w.e.f. 27-5-1976).`
  line
  line `11. Ins. by Act 29 of 1970, s. 3 (w.e.f. 12-8-1970).`
obj_root_law_sections_27_a:
  sectionId (30187)
  sectionNo 27A
  orderNo 29
  title `Alternative relief in divorce proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 68 of 1976, s. 28 (w.e.f. 27-5-1976).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908&sectionId=30187&sectionno=27A&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908
obj_root_law_sections_27_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[27A. Alternative relief in divorce proceedings.-- In any proceeding under this Act, on a petition`
  line `for dissolution of marriage by a decree of divorce, except insofar as the petition is founded on the ground`
  line `mentioned in clause (h) of sub-section (1) of section 27, the court may, if it considers it just so to do`
  line `having regard to the circumstances of the case, pass instead a decree for judicial separation.]`
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (30188)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 30
  title `Divorce by mutual consent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908&sectionId=30188&sectionno=28&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this Act and to the rules made`
  line `thereunder, a petition for divorce may be presented to the district court by both the parties together on the`
  line `ground that they have been living separately for a period of one year or more, that they have not been able`
  line `to live together and that they have mutually agreed that the marriage should be dissolved.`
  line
  line `(2)`
  line `^1[On the motion of both the parties made not earlier than six months after the date of the`
  line `presentation of the petition referred to in sub-section (1) and not later than eighteen months after the said`
  line `date, if the petition is not withdrawn in the meantime, the district court shall, on being satisfied, after`
  line `hearing the parties and after making such inquiry as it thinks fit, that a marriage has been solemnized`
  line `under this Act, and that the averments in the petition are true, pass a decree declaring the marriage to be`
  line `dissolved with effect from the date of the decree.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 29, ibid., for "On the motion of both the parties made not earlier than one year after the date of the presentation of`
  line `the petition referred to in sub-section (1) and not later than two years" (w.e.f. 27-5-1976).`
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (30189)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 31
  title `Restriction on petitions for divorce during first one year after marriage.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908&sectionId=30189&sectionno=29&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) No petition for`
  line `divorce shall be presented to the district court ^1[`
  line `unless at the date of the presentation of the petition one`
  line `year has passed] since the date of entering the certificate of marriage in the Marriage Certificate Book:`
  line
  line `Provided that the district court may, upon application being made to it, allow a petition to be`
  line `presented ^1[before one year has passed] on the ground that the case is one of exceptional hardship`
  line `suffered by the petitioner or of exceptional depravity on the part of the respondent, but if it appears to the`
  line `district court at the hearing of the petition that the petitioner obtained leave to present the petition by any`
  line `misrepresentation or concealment of the nature of the case, the district court may, if it pronounces a`
  line `decree, do so subject to the condition that the decree shall not have effect until after the`
  line `^3[expiry of one year] from the date of the marriage or may dismiss the petition, without prejudice to any petition, which`
  line `may be brought after the ^4[expiration of the said one year] upon the same, or substantially the same, facts`
  line `as those proved in support of the petition so dismissed.`
  line
  line `(2) In disposing of any application under this section for leave to present a petition for divorce before`
  line `the ^5[expiration of one year] from the date of the marriage, the district court shall have regard to the`
  line `interests of any children of the marriage, and to the question whether there is a reasonable probability of a`
  line `reconciliation between the parties before the expiration of the ^6[said one year.]`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 30, ibid., for "unless at the date of the presentation of the petition three years have passed" (w.e.f. 27-5-1976).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 30, ibid., for "before three years have passed" (w.e.f. 27-5-1976).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 30, ibid., for "expiry of three years" (w.e.f. 27-5-1976).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 30, ibid., for "expiration of the said three years" (w.e.f. 27-5-1976).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by s. 30, ibid.,for "expiration of the three years" (w.e.f. 27-5-1976).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by s. 30, ibid., for "said three years" (w.e.f. 27-5-1976).`
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (30190)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 32
  title `Remarriage of divorced persons.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes `1. The words "and one year has elapsed thereafter but not sooner" omitted by Act 68 of 1976, s. 31, (w.e.f. 27-5-1976).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908&sectionId=30190&sectionno=30&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `Where a marriage has been dissolved by a decree of divorce,`
  line `and either there is no right of appeal against the decree or if there is such a right of appeal, the time for appealing has expired without an appeal having been presented, or an appeal has been presented but has`
  line `been dismissed ^1* * * either party to the marriage may marry again.`
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (30191)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 33
  title `Court to which petition should be made.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908&sectionId=30191&sectionno=31&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `^1(1) Every petition under Chapter V or Chapter VI`
  line `shall be presented to the district court within the local limits of whose original civil jurisdiction--`
  line
  line `(i) the marriage was solemnized; or`
  line
  line `(ii) the respondent, at the time of the presentation of the petition resides; or`
  line
  line `(iii) the parties to the marriage last resided together; or`
  line
  line `^2[(iiia) in case the wife is the petitioner, where she is residing on the date of presentation of the`
  line `petition; or]`
  line
  line `(iv) the petitioner is residing at the time of the presentation of the petition, in a case where the`
  line `respondent is at that time residing outside the territories to which this Act extends, or has not been`
  line `heard of as being alive for a period of seven years by those who would naturally have heard of him if`
  line `he were alive.]`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to any jurisdiction exercisable by the court under sub-section (1), the district`
  line `court may, by virtue of this sub-section, entertain a petition by a wife domiciled in the territories to which`
  line `this Act extends for nullity of marriage or for divorce if she is resident in the said territories and has been`
  line `ordinarily resident therein for a period of three years immediately preceding the presentation of the`
  line `petition and the husband is not resident in the said territories.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 32, ibid., for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 27-5-1976).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 50 of 2003, s. 2 (w.e.f. 23-12-2003).`
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (30192)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 34
  title `Contents and verification of petitions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908&sectionId=30192&sectionno=32&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every petition under Chapter V or Chapter VI shall`
  line `state, as distinctly as the nature of the case permits the facts on which the claim to relief is founded, and`
  line `shall also state that there is no collusion between, the petitioner and the other party to the marriage.`
  line
  line `(2) The statements contained in every such petition shall be verified by the petitioner or some other`
  line `competent person in the manner required by law for the verification of plaints, and may, at the hearing, be`
  line `referred to as evidence.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (30193)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 35
  title `Proceedings to be in camera and may not be printed or published.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 68 of 1976, s. 33, for section 33 (w.e.f. 27-5-1976).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908&sectionId=30193&sectionno=33&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `^1[33. Proceedings to be in camera and may not be printed or published.-- (1) Every proceeding`
  line `under this Act shall be conducted in camera and it shall not be lawful for any person to print or publish`
  line `any matter in relation to any such proceeding except a judgment of the High Court or of the Supreme`
  line `Court printed or published with the previous permission of the Court.`
  line
  line `(2) If any person prints or publishes any matter in contravention of the provisions contained in`
  line `sub-section (1), he shall be punishable with fine which may extend to one thousand rupees.]`
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (30194)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 36
  title `Duty of court in passing decrees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908&sectionId=30194&sectionno=34&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `(1) In any proceeding under Chapter V or Chapter VI,`
  line `whether defended or not, if the court is satisfied that,--`
  line
  line `(a) any of the grounds for granting relief exists; and`
  line
  line `(b)^1[where the petition is founded on the ground specified in clause (a) of sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 27, the petitioner has not in any manner been accessory to or connived at or condoned the act`
  line `of sexual intercourse referred to therein, or, where the ground of the petition is cruelty,`
  line
  line `the petitioner has not in any manner condoned the cruelty; and`
  line
  line `(c) when divorce is sought on the ground of mutual consent, such consent has not been obtained`
  line `by force, fraud or undue influence; and`
  line
  line `(d) the petition is not presented or prosecuted in collusion with the respondent; and`
  line
  line `(e) there has not been any unnecessary or improper delay in instituting the proceedings; and`
  line
  line `(f) there is no other legal ground why the relief should not be granted;`
  line
  line `then, and in such a case, but not otherwise, the court shall decree such relief accordingly.`
  line
  line `(2) Before proceeding to grant any relief under this Act it shall be the duty of the court in the first`
  line `instance, in every case where it is possible so to do consistently with the nature and circumstances of the`
  line `case, to make every endeavour to bring about a reconciliation between the parties:`
  line
  line `^2[Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall apply to any proceeding wherein relief is`
  line `sought on any of the grounds specified in clause (c), clause (e), clause (f), clause (g) and clause (h) of subsection (1) of section 27.]`
  line
  line `^3[(3) For the purpose of aiding the court in bringing about such reconciliation, the court may, if the`
  line `parties so desire or if the court thinks it just and proper so to do, adjourn the proceedings for a reasonable`
  line `period not exceeding fifteen days and refer the matter to any person named by the parties in this behalf or`
  line `to any person nominated by the court if the parties fail to name any person, with directions to report to the`
  line `court as to whether reconciliation can be and has been, effected and the court shall in disposing of the`
  line `proceeding have due regard to the report.`
  line
  line `(4) In every case where a marriage is dissolved by a decree of divorce, the court passing the decree`
  line `shall give a copy thereof free of cost to each of the parties.]`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 34, ibid. for "where the ground of the petition is adultery, the petitioner has not in any manner been accessory to or`
  line `connived at or condoned the adultery" (w.e.f. 27-5-1976).`
  line
  line `2. Added by Act 68 of 1976, s. 34 (w.e.f. 27-5-1976).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 34, ibid. (w.e.f. 27-5-1976).`
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (30195)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 37
  title `Relief for respondent in divorce and other proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 35, ibid., for section 35 (w.e.f. 27-5-1976).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908&sectionId=30195&sectionno=35&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `^1[35. Relief for respondent in divorce and other proceedings.-- In any proceeding for divorce or`
  line `judicial separation or restitution of conjugal rights, the respondent may not only oppose the relief sought`
  line `on the ground of petitioner's adultery, cruelty or desertion, but also make a counter-claim for any relief`
  line `under this Act on that ground, and if the petitioner's adultery, cruelty or desertion is proved, the court`
  line `may give to the respondent any relief under this Act to which he or she would have been entitled if he or`
  line `she had presented a petition seeking such relief on that ground.]`
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (30196)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 38
  title `Alimony pendente lite.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 49 of 2001, s. 6 (w.e.f. 24-9-2001).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908&sectionId=30196&sectionno=36&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `Where in any proceeding under Chapter V or Chapter VI it appears to`
  line `the district court that the wife has no independent income sufficient for her support and the necessary`
  line `expenses of the proceeding, it may, on the application of the wife, order the husband to pay to her the`
  line `expenses of the proceeding, and weekly or monthly during the proceeding such sum as having regard to`
  line `the husband's income, it may seem to the court to be reasonable.`
  line
  line `^1[Provided that the application for the payment of the expenses of the proceeding and such weekly or`
  line `monthly sum during the proceeding under Chapter V or Chapter VI, shall, as far as possible, be disposed`
  line `of within sixty days from the date of service of notice on the husband.]`
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (30197)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 39
  title `Permanent alimony and maintenance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908&sectionId=30197&sectionno=37&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any court exercising jurisdiction under Chapter V`
  line `or Chapter VI may, at the time of passing any decree or at any time subsequent to the decree, on`
  line `application made to it for the purpose, order that the husband shall secure to the wife for her maintenance`
  line `and support, if necessary, by a charge on the husbands property such gross sum or such monthly or`
  line `periodical payment of money for a term not exceeding her life, as, having regard to her own property, if`
  line `any, her husbands property and ability ^1[the conduct of the parties and other circumstances of the case], it`
  line `it may seem to the court to be just.`
  line
  line `(2) If the district court is satisfied that there is a change in the circumstances of either party at any`
  line `time after it has made an order under sub-section (1), it may, at the instance of either party, vary, modify`
  line `or rescind any such order in such manner as it may seem to the court to be just.`
  line
  line `(3) If the district court is satisfied that the wife in whose favour an order has been made under this`
  line `section has remarried or is not leading a chaste life, ^2[it may, at the instance of the husband vary, modify`
  line `or rescind any such order and in such manner as the court may deem just.]`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 68 of 1976, s. 36, for "and the conduct of the parties" (w.e.f. 27-5-1976).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 68 of 1976, s. 36, for "it shall rescind the order" (w.e.f. 27-5-1976).`
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (30198)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 40
  title `Custody of children.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes `1. The proviso ins. by Act 49 of 2001, s. 7 (w.e.f. 24-9-2001).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908&sectionId=30198&sectionno=38&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `In any proceeding under Chapter V or Chapter VI the district court may,`
  line `from time to time, pass such interim orders and make such provisions in the decree as it may seem to it to`
  line `be just and proper with respect to the custody, maintenance and education of minor children, consistently`
  line `with their wishes wherever possible, and may, after the decree, upon application by petition for the`
  line `purpose, make, revoke, suspend or vary, from time to time, all such orders and provisions with respect to`
  line `the custody, maintenance and education of such children as might have been made by such decree or`
  line `interim orders in case the proceeding for obtaining such decree were still pending.`
  line
  line `^1[Provided that the application with respect to the maintenance and education of the minor children,`
  line `during the proceeding, under Chapter V or Chapter VI, shall, as far as possible, be disposed of within`
  line `sixty days from the date of service of notice on the respondent.]`
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (30199)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 41
  title `Appeals from decrees and orders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908&sectionId=30199&sectionno=39&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `^1[39. Appeals from decrees and orders-- (1) All decrees made by the court in any proceeding under`
  line `Chapter V or Chapter VI shall, subject to the provisions of sub-section (3), be appealable as decrees of the`
  line `court made in the exercise of its original civil jurisdiction, and such appeal shall lie to the court to which`
  line `appeals ordinarily lie from the decisions of the court given in the exercise of its original civil jurisdiction.`
  line
  line `(2) Orders made by the court in any proceeding under this Act, under section 37 or section 38 shall,`
  line `subject to the provisions of sub-section (3), be appealable if they are not interim orders, and every such`
  line `appeal shall lie to the court to which appeals ordinarily lie from the decisions of the court given in the`
  line `exercise of its original jurisdiction.`
  line
  line `(3) There shall be no appeal under this section on the subject of costs only.`
  line
  line `(4) Every appeal under this section shall be preferred within a ^2[period of ninety days] from the date`
  line `of the decree or order.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 68 of 1976, s. 37, for section 39 (w.e.f. 27-5-1976).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 50 of 2003, s. 3, for "period of thirty days" (w.e.f. 23-12-2003).`
obj_root_law_sections_39_a:
  sectionId (30200)
  sectionNo 39A
  orderNo 42
  title `Enforcement of decrees and orders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_a_content
  footnotes `3. Subs. by Act 68 of 1976, s. 37, for section 39 (w.e.f. 27-5-1976)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908&sectionId=30200&sectionno=39A&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908
obj_root_law_sections_39_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[39A. Enforcement of decrees and orders.-- All decrees and orders made by the court in any`
  line `proceeding under Chapter V or Chapter VI shall be enforced in the like manner as the decrees and orders`
  line `of the court made in the exercise of its original civil jurisdiction for the time being are enforced.]`
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (30201)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 43
  title `Application of Act 5 of 1908.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908&sectionId=30201&sectionno=40&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the other provisions contained in this Act, and to such`
  line `rules as the High Court may make in this behalf, all proceedings under this Act shall be regulated, as far`
  line `as may be, by the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908).`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40_a:
  sectionId (30202)
  sectionNo 40A
  orderNo 44
  title `Power to transfer petitions in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 68 of 1976, s. 38 (w.e.f. 27-5-1976).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908&sectionId=30202&sectionno=40A&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908
obj_root_law_sections_40_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[40A. Power to transfer petitions in certain cases.-- (1) Where--`
  line
  line `(a) a petition under this Act has been presented to the district court having jurisdiction, by a party`
  line `to the marriage praying for a decree for judicial separation under section 23 or for a decree of divorce`
  line `under section 27, and`
  line
  line `(b) another petition under this Act has been presented thereafter by the other party to the marriage`
  line `praying for decree for judicial separation under section 23, or for decree of divorce under section 27`
  line `on any ground whether in the same district court, or in a different district court, in the same State or in`
  line `a different State, the petition shall be dealt with as specified in sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(2) In a case where sub-section (1) applies,--`
  line
  line `(a) if the petitions are presented to the same district court, both the petitions shall be tried and`
  line `heard together by that district court;`
  line
  line `(b) if the petitions are presented to different district courts, the petitions presented later shall be`
  line `transferred to the district court in which the earlier petition was presented and both the petitions shall`
  line `be heard and disposed of together by the district court in which the earlier petition was presented.`
  line
  line `(3) In a case where clause (b) of sub-section (2) applies, the court or the Government, as the case may`
  line `be, competent under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), to transfer any suit or proceeding`
  line `from the district court in which the later petition has been presented to the district court in which the`
  line `earlier petition is pending, shall exercise its powers to transfer such later petition as if it had been`
  line `empowered so to do under the said Code.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_b:
  sectionId (30203)
  sectionNo 40B
  orderNo 45
  title `Special provisions relating to trial and disposal of petitions under the Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 68 of 1976, s. 38 (w.e.f. 27-5-1976).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908&sectionId=30203&sectionno=40B&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908
obj_root_law_sections_40_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[40B. Special provisions relating to trial and disposal of petitions under the Act.-- (1) The trial of`
  line `a petition under this Act shall, so far as is practicable consistently with the interests of justice in respect of`
  line `the trial, be continued from day to day, until its conclusions, unless the court finds the adjournment of the`
  line `trial beyond the following day to be necessary for reasons to be recorded.`
  line
  line `(2) Every petition under this Act shall be tried as expeditiously as possible and endeavour shall be`
  line `made to conclude the trial within six months from the date of service of notice of the petition on the`
  line respondent.
  line
  line `(3) Every appeal under this Act shall be heard as expeditiously as possible, and endeavour shall be`
  line `made to conclude the hearing within three months from the date of service of notice of appeal on the`
  line respondent.]
obj_root_law_sections_40_c:
  sectionId (30204)
  sectionNo 40C
  orderNo 46
  title `Documentary evidence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_c_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 68 of 1976, s. 38 (w.e.f. 27-5-1976).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908&sectionId=30204&sectionno=40C&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908
obj_root_law_sections_40_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[40C. Documentary evidence-- Notwithstanding anything contained in any enactment to the`
  line `contrary, no document shall be inadmissible in evidence in any proceeding at the trial of a petition under`
  line `this Act on the ground that it is not duly stamped or registered.]`
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (30205)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 47
  title `Power of High Court to make rules regulating procedure.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908&sectionId=30205&sectionno=41&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `(1) The High Court shall, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, make such rules consistent with the provisions contained in this Act`
  line `and the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), as it may consider expedient for the purpose of`
  line `carrying into effect the provisions of Chapters V, VI and VII.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing provision, such rules shall`
  line `provide for,--`
  line
  line `(a) the impleading by the petitioner of the adulterer as a co-respondent on a petition for divorce`
  line `on the ground of adultery, and the circumstances in which the petitioner may be execused from doing`
  line so;
  line
  line `(b) the awarding of damages against any such co-respondent;`
  line
  line `(c) the intervention in any proceeding under Chapter V or Chapter VI by any person not already a`
  line `party thereto;`
  line
  line `(d) the form and contents of petitions for nullity of marriage or for divorce and the payment of`
  line `costs incurred by parties to such petitions; and`
  line
  line `(e) any other matter for which no provision or no sufficient provision is made in this Act, and for`
  line `which provision is made in the Indian Divorce Act, 1869 (4 of 1869).`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (30206)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 48
  title Saving.
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908&sectionId=30206&sectionno=42&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `Nothing contained in this Act shall affect the validity of any marriage not solemnized`
  line `under its provisions; nor shall this Act be deemed directly or indirectly to affect the validity of any mode`
  line `of contracting marriage.`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (30207)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 49
  title `Penalty on married person marrying again under this Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908&sectionId=30207&sectionno=43&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `Save as otherwise provided in`
  line `Chapter III, every person who, being at the time married, procures, a marriage of himself or herself to be`
  line `solemnized under this Act shall be deemed to have committed an offence under section 494 or section`
  line `495 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860), as the case may be, and the marriage so solemnized shall be`
  line void.
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (30208)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 50
  title `Punishment of bigamy.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908&sectionId=30208&sectionno=44&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `Every person whose marriage is solemnized under this Act and who,`
  line `during the lifetime of his or her wife or husband, contracts any other marriage shall be subject to the`
  line `penalties provided in section 494 and section 495 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860), for the offence`
  line `of marrying again during the lifetime of a husband or wife, and the marriage so contracted shall be void.`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (30209)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 51
  title `Penalty for signing false declaration or certificate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908&sectionId=30209&sectionno=45&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `Every person making, signing or attesting`
  line `any declaration or certificate required by or under this Act containing a statement which is false and`
  line `which he either knows or believes to be false or does not believe to be true shall be guilty of the offence`
  line `described in section 199 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (30210)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 52
  title `Penalty for wrongful action of Marriage Officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908&sectionId=30210&sectionno=46&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `Any Marriage Officer who knowingly and`
  line `wilfully solemnizes a marriage under this Act,--`
  line
  line `(1) without publishing a notice regarding such marriage as required by section 5, or`
  line
  line `(2) within thirty days of the publication of the notice of such marriage, or`
  line
  line `(3) in contravention of any other provision in this Act,`
  line
  line `shall be punishable with simple imprisonment for a term which may extend to one year, or with fine`
  line `which may extend to five hundred rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (30211)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 53
  title `Marriage Certificate Book to be open to inspection.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908&sectionId=30211&sectionno=47&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Marriage Certificate Book kept`
  line `under this Act shall at all reasonable times be open for inspection and shall be admissible as evidence of`
  line `the statements therein contained.`
  line
  line `(2) Certified extracts from the Marriage Certificate Book shall, on application, be given by the`
  line `Marriage Officer to the applicant on payment by him of the prescribed fee.`
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (30212)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 54
  title `Transmission of copies of entries in marriage records.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908&sectionId=30212&sectionno=48&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `Every Marriage Officer in a State`
  line `shall send to Registrar-General of Births, Deaths and Marriages of that State at such intervals and in such`
  line `form as may be prescribed, a true copy of all entries made by him in the Marriage Certificate Book since`
  line `the last of such intervals, and, in the case of Marriage Officers outside the territories to which this Act`
  line `extends, the true copy shall be sent to such authority as the Central Government may specify in this`
  line behalf.
obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (30213)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 55
  title `Correction of errors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908&sectionId=30213&sectionno=49&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any Marriage Officer who discovers any error in the form or`
  line `substance of any entry in the Marriage Certificate Book may, within one month next after the discovery of`
  line `such error, in the presence of the persons married or, in case of their death or absence, in the presence of`
  line `two other credible witnesses, correct the error by entry in the margin without any alteration of the original`
  line `entry and shall sign the marginal entry and add thereto the date of such correction and the Marriage`
  line `Officer shall make the like marginal entry in the certificate thereof.`
  line
  line `(2) Every correction made under this section shall be attested by the witnesses in whose presence it`
  line `was made.`
  line
  line `(3) Where a copy of any entry has already been sent under section 48 to the Registrar-General or`
  line `other authority the Marriage Officer shall make and send in like manner a separate certificate of the`
  line `original erroneous entry and of the marginal corrections therein made.`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (30214)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 56
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908&sectionId=30214&sectionno=50&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government, in the case of ^1* * * officers of the Central`
  line `Government, and the State Government, in all other cases, may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules for carrying out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the duties and powers of Marriage Officers and the areas in which they may exercise`
  line jurisdiction;
  line
  line `(b) the manner in which a Marriage Officer may hold inquiries under this Act and the procedure`
  line therefor;
  line
  line `(c) the form and manner in which any books required by or under this Act shall be maintained;`
  line
  line `(d) the fees that may be levied for the performance of any duty imposed upon a Marriage Officer`
  line `under this Act;`
  line
  line `(e) the manner in which public notice shall be given under section 16;`
  line
  line `(f) the form in which, and the intervals within which, copies of entries in the Marriage Certificate`
  line `Book shall be sent in pursuance of section 48;`
  line
  line `(g) any other matter which may be or requires to be prescribed.`
  line
  line `^2[(3) Every rule made by the Central Government under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after`
  line `it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which`
  line `may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the`
  line `session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in`
  line `making any modification in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall`
  line `thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that`
  line `any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done`
  line `under that rule.`
  line
  line `(4) Every rule made by the State Government under this Act shall be laid, as soon as it is made before`
  line `the State Legislature.]`
obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "diplomatic and consular officers and other" omitted by Act 33 of 1969, s. 29 (w.e.f. 31-8-1969).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 20 of 1983, s. 2 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 15.3.1984).`
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (30215)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 57
  title `Repeals and savings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908&sectionId=30215&sectionno=51&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00019_195443_1517807321908
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Special Marriage Act, 1872 (3 of 1872), and any law`
  line `corresponding to the Special Marriage Act, 1872 (3 of 1872), in force in any Part B State immediately`
  line `before the commencement of this Act are hereby repealed.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding such repeal,--`
  line
  line `(a) all marriages duly solemnized under the Special Marriage Act, 1872 (3 of 1872), or any such`
  line `corresponding law shall be deemed to have been solemnized under this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) all suits and proceedings in causes and matters matrimonial which, when this Act comes into`
  line `operation, are pending in any court, shall be dealt with and decided by such court, so far as may be, as`
  line `if they had been originally instituted therein under this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) The provisions of sub-section (2) shall be without prejudice to the provisions contained in section`
  line `6 of the General Clauses Act, 1897 (10 of 1897), which shall also apply to the repeal of the corresponding`
  line `law as if such corresponding law had been an enactment.`
obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes:
  string
  line
